Data Direction Register		$0000Peripheral Data Register	$0001	-DDR maps PDR bits to inputs or outputs	-DDR bit value of 1, means PDR bit value is outputted to I/O device	-DDR bit value of 0, means PDR bit value is inputted from I/O deviceDDR and PDR		---------------------------------register bit		| 7 | 6 | 5 | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 |default values		---------------------------------DDR = xx101111		0 - LORAMPDR = xx110111		1 - HIRAM			2 - CHAREN			3 - Cassette write data			4 - Cassette sense (0 = PLAY button depressed)			5 - Cassette motor control (0 = motor spins)			6 - unused (not available on the 6510)			7 - unused (not available on the 6510)			  -------------------------------			  *** M E M O R Y   M O D E S ***			  -------------------------------0111			    (LORAM, HIRAM, GAME, EXROM)			   	xx11C11       | DEFAULT		 011x					ULTIMAX       | 1111	 101x	 1000	 00x0	 001x	 1110	 0100	 1100	 xx01-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| SOFT  | YES   | YES   | NO    | YES   | YES   | NO    | NO    | NO    | NO    |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| GAME  | YES   | YES   | NO    | YES   | YES   | YES   | NO    | NO    | NO    |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $0000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $1000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $2000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $3000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $4000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $5000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $6000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $7000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $8000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ROML  | RAM   | ROML  | ROML* |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $9000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ROML  | RAM   | ROML  | ROML* |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $A000 | BASIC | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | BASIC | ROMH  | ROMH  | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $B000 | BASIC | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | BASIC | ROMH  | ROMH  | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $C000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   | ---   |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $D000 | IO/C  | IO/C  | IO/RAM| IO/C  | RAM   | IO/C  | IO/C  | IO/C  | IO    |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $E000 | KERNAL| RAM   | RAM   | KERNAL| RAM   | KERNAL| KERNAL| KERNAL| ROMH* |-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------|-------| $F000 | KERNAL| RAM   | RAM   | KERNAL| RAM   | KERNAL| KERNAL| KERNAL| ROMH* |  	*) Internal memory does not respond to write accesses to these areas. Legend:-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------ Kernal | $E000 - $FFFF	| Kernal ROM.-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------IO/C   | $D000 - $DFFF	| I/O address space or Character       |		| generator ROM, selected by -CHAREN.       |		| If the CHAREN bit is clear,       |		| the character generator ROM is       |		| chosen. If it is set, the       |		| I/O chips are accessible.-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------IO/RAM | $D000 - $DFFF	| I/O address space or RAM,       |		| selected by -CHAREN.       |		| If the CHAREN bit is clear,       |		| the character generator ROM is       |		| chosen. If it is set, the       |		| internal RAM is accessible.-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------IO     | $D000 - $DFFF	| I/O address space.       |		| The -CHAREN line has no effect.-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------BASIC  | $A000 - $BFFF	| BASIC ROM.-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------ROMH   | $A000 - $BFFF	| External ROM with the -ROMH line       |      or	| connected to its -CS line.       | $E000 - $FFFF	|-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------ROML   | $8000 - $9FFF	| External ROM with the -ROML line       |		| connected to its -CS line.-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------RAM    | various ranges	| Commodore 64's internal RAM.-------|----------------|---------------------------------------------------------    | $1000 - $7FFF	| Open address space.        |      or	| The Commodore 64's memory chips       | $A000 - $CFFF  | do not detect any memory accesses       |		| to this area except the VIC-II's       |		| DMA and memory refreshes.